# useColor

`useColor` is a custom hook used to get the theme color by the given path, we can add `light` or `dark` prefix to get the specific color mode value.

## Import

```jsx live=false
import { useColor } from '@node-real/bee';
```

## Usage

```jsx
function Example() {
  const bg1 = useColor('bg.top.normal'); // current color mode value
  const bg2 = useColor('light.scene.warning.normal', 0.5); // light color mode value
  const color = useColor('dark.readable.secondary'); // dark color mode value

  return (
    <Box bg={bg1} h={40}>
      <Box bg={bg2} color={color} w={100} h={40}>
        Some text
      </Box>
    </Box>
  );
}
```

## Arguments

<PropsTable
  data={[
    {
      name: 'path',
      required: true,
      type: 'string',
      default: '',
      desc: 'The path to visit the color.',
    },
    {
      name: 'opacity',
      required: false,
      type: 'number',
      default: 1,
      desc: 'Color opacity',
    },
  ]}
/>

